                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.332/1: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Uruguay</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grant-Smith</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-10-11T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 11, 1926—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>24. With reference to Legation’s despatch No. 287, September 6, you may say in
                    your discretion to the Acting Foreign Minister that <pb facs="0917" n="815"
                        xml:id="pg_815"/> you had reported your conversation to the Department and
                    that you had been authorized to submit draft of treaty if such a course would
                    now be acceptable. Should the Department receive a telegram from you stating
                    that you had received an affirmative reply, whether oral or written, it will
                    endeavor to forward draft of treaty by next pouch.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
